# Camera Surveillance Car

## Project Description
The Camera Surveillance Car is a mobile robotic vehicle equipped with a camera for real-time video monitoring.
It can be controlled wirelessly using a web interface and is used for security and surveillance applications.

## Objectives
- To design a mobile surveillance system
- To enable real-time video streaming
- To control the vehicle remotely
- To improve security monitoring

## Hardware Requirements
- ESP32 / ESP32-CAM
- DC Motors
- Motor Driver (L298N / L293D)
- Camera Module
- Chassis
- Battery
- Jumper Wires

## Software Requirements
- Arduino IDE
- Embedded C / Arduino
- Wi-Fi
- Web Browser

## Working Principle
The ESP32 controls the motors using a motor driver.
The camera streams live video over Wi-Fi.
The user can view the live feed and control the car through a browser.

## Applications
- Home security
- Industrial surveillance
- Military monitoring
- Disaster management

## Conclusion
This project provides a low-cost and efficient mobile surveillance solution using wireless communication and embedded systems.
